data.meta_description: MK40 4PU is a residential postcode in Queens Park, Bedford. Check typical house prices, council tax bands, business rates, broadband availability and local schools. Find nearby hotels and holiday rentals.
data.text:
Summary

MK40 4PU is a residential postcode in Queens Park, Bedford. It was first introduced in January 1993.

The most common council tax band is A.

Residential buildings are typically detached and terraced (including end-terrace). Domestic properties are primarily flats.

Residential buildings were typically constructed between 1991 and 1995 and between 1983 and 1990.

Domestic properties are predominantly social housing.

The most common Energy Performance Certificate (EPC) ratings are C and D.

Bedford is a town, which had a population of 87,590 in the 2011 census.

In the 2011 census, there were 16 people resident in MK40 4PU, of which 12 were male and 4 were female. This includes overnight visitors as well as permanent residents.

MK40 4PU is in the Bedford travel to work area. NHS services are provided by the Bedfordshire Primary Care Trust.

MK40 4PU is approximately 34m (112ft) above sea level.
